The paper discusses a comparison study of two nonlinear control schemes, which suggests that it could belong to the Control Engineering (cs.CE) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The use of linear parameter-varying (LPV) models and Control Contraction Metrics (CCMs) also suggests that it could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the comparison study may involve data analysis and modeling, which could also place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
